						               													<description>Caliber .45 is a game about wild west, cowboys, caravans and trains robbery, skirmishes and betrayals, all for the sake of the cherished million. Caliber .45 serves great for party board gaming. It can be played against each other, or divided into teams.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The essence of the game&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each player receives a cowboy card, then the cowboys take turns arming themselves, collecting cards from a common deck with weapons. One of the players, realizing that he is ready to go into the business, notifies other players and they can decide either to join the raid or refuse. Cowboys-robbers draw out a card of their target - it can be a stagecoach, train, bank or other card that brings money - then they will need to get rid of security, by spending their weapons. After that cowboys begin to divide the loot, which most often leads to a shootout, the winner receives the whole jackpot. In the loot deck there are not only trains and stagecoaches, there are also indians, a sheriff and other misfortunes that can ruin a robbery, send robbers to prison, or even kill an entire gang at once.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The cowboy's task is to earn his million. The one whose extraction brought this money becomes the winner.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;You can play the game alone against all or teams, teaming up in pairs, in which case you will need to collect a million for two.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Who is this game for?&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The board game is suitable for parties, table feasts in canyons and deserts, behind the bar of the saloon or family evenings on the farm. You can give it to children and adults, especially suitable for those who like simple games for the company, cowboy themes and spaghetti westerns, competitive card fillers, mustangs and armadillos.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
